hopobject.body:
Expand the Capabilities of your BeagleBone

The BeagleBone mikroBUS Cape allows users to connect up to four of mikroElektronika click boards to the BeagleBone and BeagleBone Black.

 

Currently there are over 90 click boards to choose from and the list is constantly expanding.

 

Pick and mix from over 90 click Boards 

As an example, you can pick and mix from the following list of click boards to have four capes in one:

  1. RS485 click

  2. RS232 click

  3. CAN click

  4. Relay click

  5. RTC click

  6. Accel click (Accelerometer)

  7. Gyro click (Gryoscope)

  8. LED click (LED Matrix)

  9. Expand click

 

For a full list of available click boards visit: www.tigal.com

 

 

Main Features

  • Cape provides 4 click board interfaces

  • Over 90 click boards available and counting

  • All essential pins covered

  • Simple design

  • Currently Supports only 3.3V click boards

  • Ideal for breadboards too!

Important Links:

  1. To purchase or find a local reseller visit www.tigal.com. 

  2. For more information about mikroBUS Standard, visit: http://www.mikroe.com/mikrobus/. 

  3. C Code examples for all clicks are available at: http://www.libstock.com/.

  4. mikroBUS Cape WIKI Pages: https://www.tigal.com/wiki/doku.php?id=tigalcapes:bb_mikrobus_cape.  

What is mikroBUS?

 

mikroBUS is a specially designed pinout standard with SPI, I2C, Analog, UART, Interrupt, PWM, Reset and Power supply pins. It has two 1x8 headers, each with VCC and GND power supply pads. 

New Click Boards featuring the mikroBUS pinout standard are released every month. It is worth coming back every now and then to check what new click boards have become available recently.
